\f0\fs26 \cf0 I want some software to restore key files, application configurations, determine the bespoke software installed when I move to my new Mac Book Air with a M5 processor, 32 GB of memory and 1TB of storage. Most of my own files are stored in Google Drive so they don\'92t need backing up. Can you produce a script that backs up important information and then restores them on a new computer? I want the following to be done as a minimum but please prompt me with ideas of what else would be useful. Write any files needed in the folder /Users/iain/restore_osx not in /mnt. There are two early versions of command-line scripts backup.sh and restore.sh. You could start again from these but you could also start again with a new command line version or python scripts.\
